WEBVTT

00:56.770 --> 00:58.147
Derrick Reed.

00:58.313 --> 00:59.781
In my mom's helicopter.

00:59.940 --> 01:01.988
Yes way.

01:02.150 --> 01:03.948
Yeah, Hallie's skiing up
on the mountain.

01:04.944 --> 01:06.947
Right?
Like out of all places, here.

01:07.114 --> 01:09.242
No, it is Christmas.
I insist.

01:09.408 --> 01:10.625
I can absolutely do it myself.

01:10.784 --> 01:13.458
<i>- </i> I fly that route all the time.

01:13.620 --> 01:14.963
No.

01:15.122 --> 01:16.669
Hey, can someone
answer the door?

01:21.003 --> 01:22.380
Mo.

01:22.546 --> 01:25.095
I can't believe it.

01:25.257 --> 01:26.258
Jennifer.

01:26.425 --> 01:28.928
<i>- </i> What?
- The door.

01:29.928 --> 01:31.930
I gotta go-

01:32.097 --> 01:34.441
My rodent of a brother isn't old enough
to answer the door.

01:34.600 --> 01:37.069
I don't know who the kid is,
but apparently he's a big deal.

01:37.227 --> 01:38.979
Jennifer can barely
contain herself.

01:39.146 --> 01:40.272
Mo!

01:40.439 --> 01:41.861
Rudy!

01:42.024 --> 01:43.651
I'm kinda busy up here!

01:45.027 --> 01:47.450
Rudy, a little help here!

01:47.613 --> 01:49.661
Calm down.
It's okay, Mo.

01:52.451 --> 01:54.169
Mo.

01:56.830 --> 01:58.173
Hey, who is it?

01:58.332 --> 02:02.053
Mo, quit it.

02:03.045 --> 02:04.547
It's a gift.

02:04.713 --> 02:06.715
Well, say thank you.

02:06.882 --> 02:08.976
It's heavy.

02:09.133 --> 02:11.557
Maybe it's my Dragon of
the Crown expansion set.

02:11.720 --> 02:14.189
It's probably another fruitcake.

02:20.020 --> 02:21.693
Hi, Sam!

02:21.855 --> 02:23.857
Such a beautiful tree.

02:24.024 --> 02:25.697
Hey, Danny.
Merry Christmas.

02:25.859 --> 02:27.019
Yeah, I'm so glad we got that.

02:27.027 --> 02:28.067
It was the last one there.

02:28.195 --> 02:30.035
- Are you okay with it?
- Yeah, yeah, I'm good.

02:38.372 --> 02:41.376
And you have a merry Christmas.

02:41.541 --> 02:42.838
Thanks.

02:43.001 --> 02:45.424
- Fred.
- John.

02:45.587 --> 02:47.760
I see you still haven't fixed
the town clock.

02:47.923 --> 02:50.392
Well, what can I say?
Time got away on me.

02:50.550 --> 02:52.723
Yeah, well.
You and me both.

02:52.886 --> 02:54.646
You think we're gonna have
a white Christmas?

02:54.763 --> 02:57.016
No snow.
Weird, huh?

02:58.558 --> 03:00.185
Gifts are all packed up.

03:01.186 --> 03:04.235
Some of them still aren't
wrapped yet, but...

03:05.399 --> 03:07.618
That's great.
Beth'll be thrilled.

03:07.776 --> 03:11.155
Sure is nice that she commits
to doing this every year.

03:11.321 --> 03:13.073
Well, I guess there are people
who need a lot more than we do.

03:13.240 --> 03:14.708
We're lucky here, Fred.

03:14.866 --> 03:17.619
That we are.
That we are.

03:17.786 --> 03:19.629
Hey, did that game come in
that I ordered for Rudy'?

03:19.788 --> 03:22.917
I was kinda hoping he'd have it
for a stocking stuffer.

03:23.083 --> 03:26.587
Dragon of the Crown
expansion set.

03:26.753 --> 03:28.676
Still on back order, I'm afraid.

03:28.839 --> 03:31.467
I don't have high hopes of it
being here for the holiday.

03:31.633 --> 03:33.135
If that's the worst problem
I have in my house

03:33.301 --> 03:35.349
this Christmas,
then I'm better off than most.

03:35.512 --> 03:37.640
You got that right.

03:37.806 --> 03:39.479
All right.

03:39.641 --> 03:41.814
My regards to the family.

03:41.977 --> 03:43.650
Yeah, will do.

03:43.812 --> 03:45.439
What about headwinds?
What about flight range?

03:45.605 --> 03:47.325
I know it's a lot of weight
to fly that far,

03:47.441 --> 03:49.401
but we can't let them down.
It's tough over there.

03:49.443 --> 03:50.945
A lot of families
are counting on the help.

03:51.111 --> 03:52.613
Yeah, I know, but, uh...

03:52.779 --> 03:54.122
Lawrenceville's a ways away.

03:54.281 --> 03:56.750
No, we got the room and, yes,
the forecast looks fine.

03:56.908 --> 03:58.285
So quit worrying.

04:01.037 --> 04:02.539
What's this?

04:02.706 --> 04:03.923
That's the one I was telling
you about.

04:04.082 --> 04:06.301
Someone must have dropped it off
this afternoon.

04:06.460 --> 04:09.634
- No name, no address.
- Hmm.

04:10.630 --> 04:11.847
No name, no address.

04:12.007 --> 04:13.554
Honey, maybe it was
for Lawrenceville.

04:13.717 --> 04:15.094
No, it's not marked for that,

04:15.260 --> 04:17.228
and all of those went
to Fred's store.

04:17.387 --> 04:18.934
It's from Santa.

04:19.096 --> 04:20.817
Santa brings gifts
down the chimney, stupid.

04:20.932 --> 04:22.980
- Hey.
- I think we should open it.

04:23.143 --> 04:25.316
The two of you.
Honestly.

04:29.691 --> 04:31.443
What do you think it is?

04:34.321 --> 04:36.244
I think maybe it's
a set of golf clubs.

04:36.406 --> 04:37.953
- Mm. Mm-hmm.
- Dad.

04:38.116 --> 04:39.789
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

04:39.951 --> 04:42.670
So, Mom...

04:42.829 --> 04:44.456
Yes?

04:44.623 --> 04:46.503
Do you think you're gonna need
any help tomorrow

04:46.666 --> 04:48.418
with the helicopter and stuff?

04:48.585 --> 04:50.633
Yeah, I think I got it covered, honey.

04:50.796 --> 04:52.173
You said Tim wasn't
going with you.

04:52.339 --> 04:55.013
Please, Mom.
Come on.

04:58.011 --> 05:00.184
Oh, for crying out loud.
Just open it.

05:07.646 --> 05:10.240
What is wrong
with that dog today?

05:10.398 --> 05:12.821
Wow.

05:12.984 --> 05:15.203
- That is cool.
- Yeah.

05:27.040 --> 05:29.384
It's so gorgeous.

05:29.543 --> 05:32.137
- Boring.
- No, no, no, no, come on.

05:32.295 --> 05:34.263
Look at the craftsmanship
in this thing.

05:35.257 --> 05:37.385
There's Main Street.

05:37.551 --> 05:39.224
There's Town Hall.

05:40.220 --> 05:41.642
The clock on the tower's
stuck on the same time

05:41.805 --> 05:42.897
as the real clock.

05:48.478 --> 05:50.401
- I'll get it.

05:55.235 --> 05:56.452
Pizza's here!

06:02.909 --> 06:04.627
It looks like, uh...

06:41.990 --> 06:43.116
Ah!

06:43.283 --> 06:44.626
Move!

06:45.869 --> 06:46.995
Everybody off the street!

06:47.162 --> 06:49.540
Move, move!
Come on, let's go!

06:49.706 --> 06:51.458
Move!
Move!

07:17.984 --> 07:20.032
You feel that?

07:20.195 --> 07:21.993
Yeah, was that a tremor?

07:26.826 --> 07:28.078
Yeah, hey, Tully.

07:29.079 --> 07:30.831
Yeah, we did.

07:30.997 --> 07:32.499
Yeah, I'll be right there.

07:33.500 --> 07:35.093
<i>- </i> Something happened downtown.
- Okay.

07:35.251 --> 07:36.719
- I'll call you.
- Yeah.

07:41.841 --> 07:43.218
No one come any closer.

07:43.385 --> 07:46.104
You don't want to be near this
if there's another aftershock.

07:49.349 --> 07:50.521
Tully.

07:52.018 --> 07:54.737
John, over here.

07:56.731 --> 07:57.857
Wow.

07:58.024 --> 07:59.571
Yeah.

08:00.568 --> 08:02.946
<i>- </i> Any injuries?
- I don't think so.

08:03.113 --> 08:05.115
We got lucky.

08:05.281 --> 08:06.783
All right,
let's get those fires out.

08:06.950 --> 08:08.042
Cordon this off.

08:08.201 --> 08:09.418
I got some rope in my trunk.

08:17.877 --> 08:20.551
Oh, my God.
I think that's Jacob.

08:39.482 --> 08:41.780
Rudy?

08:44.236 --> 08:45.580
What are you doing awake?

08:45.739 --> 08:47.958
I can't sleep.

08:48.116 --> 08:50.619
Sweetheart,
I have a really early morning.

08:50.785 --> 08:52.583
Your dad's gonna be busy
all day tomorrow.

08:54.372 --> 08:56.591
We all need our rest, okay?

08:56.750 --> 08:58.093
- Okay'
- OK?!/'

08:58.251 --> 08:59.844
<i>- </i> Mo, come on. Come on, boy.

09:00.003 --> 09:01.255
Come on.

09:01.421 --> 09:03.173
I love you.

09:03.339 --> 09:05.683
Love you, too.

09:28.031 --> 09:30.033
Rudy's still in bed, lazy bum.

09:30.200 --> 09:32.328
Yeah, he was up past midnight.

09:32.494 --> 09:33.711
We'll let him sleep.

09:33.870 --> 09:35.463
Mary'll be by to look after him.

09:36.623 --> 09:37.966
So much for good weather.

09:41.294 --> 09:43.046
It'll be fine.

09:44.339 --> 09:46.467
I do this a dozen times a year.

09:49.385 --> 09:50.557
Yeah, I guess you should go.

09:50.720 --> 09:52.097
The kids in Lawrenceville
would be disappointed

09:52.263 --> 09:53.355
if you didn't show up.

09:53.515 --> 09:55.313
And I'm gonna let
Jacob's brother know.

09:55.475 --> 09:56.897
What about Jacob?

09:57.060 --> 09:59.813
Wow, look at you helping.

09:59.979 --> 10:01.105
Can't a daughterjust

10:01.272 --> 10:03.149
help her mother once in a while?

10:05.902 --> 10:08.576
Mom, I'm begging you.
It's Derrick Reed.

10:08.738 --> 10:09.990
He's a client.

10:10.156 --> 10:11.499
I'll be good.
I promise.

10:11.658 --> 10:12.705
And besides,

10:12.867 --> 10:14.995
I can help with dropping off
the gifts afterwards.

10:15.995 --> 10:17.463
<i>- </i> Please?
- Who's Derrick Reed?

10:17.622 --> 10:19.044
Only the best snowboarder ever.

10:19.207 --> 10:20.584
Ah, wow.

10:20.750 --> 10:22.627
- Best ever, Beth.
<i>- </i> Mm.

10:24.629 --> 10:27.348
Where I am going is very remote.

10:27.507 --> 10:29.851
And I have
a very strict schedule.

10:30.009 --> 10:31.761
Well, without Tim, you are solo.

10:31.928 --> 10:33.521
Right?

10:38.518 --> 10:40.441
Get your coat.

10:40.603 --> 10:41.980
Thanks.

10:42.147 --> 10:43.694
- I love you.
- Uh-huh.

10:43.857 --> 10:45.029
Hey, how about
a little love over here?

10:45.191 --> 10:46.693
I'm the one who made it happen.

10:48.319 --> 10:50.037
Hey, listen.
Uh...

10:50.196 --> 10:51.493
that gift you got your brother.

10:51.656 --> 10:53.499
That was nice of you.

10:53.658 --> 10:54.705
Did Fred make that?

10:54.868 --> 10:56.415
Dad, I didn't get that gift.

10:56.578 --> 10:58.080
But if you want,
I'll take the credit.

11:02.083 --> 11:03.460
All right.

11:03.626 --> 11:05.219
<i>- </i> You be safe.
- You be safe.

11:06.880 --> 11:09.053
Mistletoe.

11:11.217 --> 11:12.560
Wait.

11:12.719 --> 11:15.222
- No mistletoe.
- Ew, gross.

11:15.388 --> 11:17.311
- I love you.
- See you soon.

11:17.473 --> 11:19.146
Get in the car.

11:34.157 --> 11:35.454
Hey, Champ.

11:35.617 --> 11:37.961
Hey, how you doing, buddy?

11:38.119 --> 11:39.416
Hey, Dad?

11:39.579 --> 11:41.297
Did the ground break last night?

11:41.456 --> 11:44.255
Yeah, I guess
you could say that.

11:44.417 --> 11:46.761
- Hey, Rudy. Hey, Mr. M.
- Hey, Mary.

11:46.920 --> 11:48.297
Hi, Mary.
Thanks for the last-minute help.

11:48.463 --> 11:50.465
Dad, I wanna see where
the ground broke.

11:51.466 --> 11:53.434
It's too dangerous
right now, buddy.

11:53.593 --> 11:56.221
How'd you know the ground broke,
anyway, Mr. Big Ears?

11:57.222 --> 11:59.190
I-I saw it in the snow globe.

11:59.349 --> 12:00.817
In the snow globe?

12:00.975 --> 12:03.603
<i>- </i> Really?
- Yeah.

12:04.729 --> 12:06.449
I'll have to check that out
when I get back.

12:08.775 --> 12:10.197
Bye, Mr. M.

12:10.360 --> 12:12.078
Hey, no sneaking a look
at the gifts under the tree.

12:12.237 --> 12:14.660
Bye, Dad.

12:14.822 --> 12:17.291
Let's see what kind of trouble
we can get ourselves into.

12:26.501 --> 12:28.503
Aren't they supposed
to be here by now?

12:28.670 --> 12:30.217
Yeah.
Listen, I know you're excited.

12:30.380 --> 12:32.974
When they get here, I want you
to be extremely professional.

12:33.132 --> 12:34.304
What's that supposed to mean?

12:34.467 --> 12:36.140
No ogling, no drooling.

12:36.302 --> 12:37.804
Mom, really?

12:41.474 --> 12:43.977
They're here.

13:04.080 --> 13:06.003
Ho ho ho.

13:06.165 --> 13:07.382
<i>- </i> Are you Beth?
- Yeah.

13:07.542 --> 13:09.340
- Hey, I'm Derrick Reed.
- Pleasure.

13:09.502 --> 13:11.382
<i>- </i> Hey, I'm Greg.
- Hi, hello. Good to meet you.

13:11.796 --> 13:13.969
This is, uh,
this is my assistant Jennifer.

13:14.966 --> 13:17.845
Oh, hi, Jennifer.
Happy holidays.

13:18.845 --> 13:20.563
Happy holidays, indeed.

13:20.722 --> 13:23.441
So are you guys looking
for anything in particular?

13:23.599 --> 13:25.476
Oh, you know.
Just some choice powder.

13:25.643 --> 13:27.020
- A good incline.
- Yeah, you know the mountain

13:27.186 --> 13:28.466
- better than we do.
- All right.

13:28.604 --> 13:29.901
Let's get you guys loaded up

13:30.064 --> 13:32.408
and stop wasting daylight.

13:32.567 --> 13:34.035
<i>- </i> Cool.
- Yeah. Okay.

13:34.193 --> 13:35.570
- Okay.
- Do you need help

13:35.737 --> 13:38.411
<i>- </i> with your stuff?
- Uh, yeah.

13:38.573 --> 13:39.699
That would be great...

13:39.866 --> 13:42.369
Actually, I need you to do
a final rundown on the engine.

13:43.661 --> 13:45.254
Hey, no sweat.

13:45.413 --> 13:47.541
Yeah, we can handle it.

13:50.251 --> 13:52.299
What?
I wasn't ogling.

13:52.462 --> 13:55.557
No, you were flirting,
which is way worse than ogling.

13:55.715 --> 13:57.592
What did I say?

13:57.759 --> 14:01.059
All right, dude.
Let's do this.

14:12.774 --> 14:14.151
Tully.

14:14.317 --> 14:16.490
<i>HEY</i>

14:18.112 --> 14:19.659
<i>- </i> Coffee fresh?
- Fresh, yes.

14:19.822 --> 14:22.245
Good?
That's another story.

14:22.408 --> 14:23.768
Filled in
most of the smaller ones.

14:23.910 --> 14:25.287
Roped off the larger one
for now.

14:26.913 --> 14:29.132
So, where are we at with damage?

14:29.290 --> 14:31.167
Well, the gas mains are intact.

14:31.334 --> 14:33.553
Which is surprising, considering
the flames everyone mentioned.

14:33.711 --> 14:35.384
Maybe a natural gas pocket.

14:35.546 --> 14:36.986
What about Grainer
and Lawrenceville?

14:37.048 --> 14:39.972
Yeah, nothing. They didn't
even know we had a tremor.

14:41.094 --> 14:43.142
<i>- </i> Even in Grainer?
- Yeah.

14:43.304 --> 14:45.022
As far as anyone
outside of town knows,

14:45.181 --> 14:47.525
that earthquake never
even happened.

14:48.518 --> 14:51.488
- That's impossible.
- I know. It's strange, huh?

14:55.441 --> 14:56.801
Come on.
Let's get this cleaned up.

14:56.943 --> 14:58.945
All right.

15:19.465 --> 15:21.888
Hey, did the rotor heads
check out?

15:22.051 --> 15:23.598
The what?

15:24.887 --> 15:27.481
You don't know anything
about helicopters, do you?

15:27.640 --> 15:29.142
No.

15:32.186 --> 15:33.813
She's your mom, isn't she?

15:38.651 --> 15:41.746
Hey, you want me
to sign something?

15:43.656 --> 15:45.249
Yeah?

15:46.993 --> 15:48.495
Here.

15:50.163 --> 15:51.961
Right there?

15:59.005 --> 16:00.678
It's nice, honey.

16:32.413 --> 16:34.256
<i>- </i> Come on, man. Put that away.
- What are you talking about?

16:34.415 --> 16:36.415
<i>- </i> This is what we came here for.
- All right, man.

16:38.878 --> 16:40.380
<i>- </i> Good?
- Yeah.

16:44.467 --> 16:46.265
What's up, boys and girls?

16:46.427 --> 16:48.054
We're fresh out of reindeer,

16:48.221 --> 16:50.223
but Santa's always
got his sleigh.

16:51.224 --> 16:52.521
Good?

16:52.683 --> 16:54.981
<i>- </i> That's fantastic.
- All right, dude.

16:55.144 --> 16:56.817
Let's do this.

17:02.151 --> 17:03.903
Whoo-hoo!

17:05.738 --> 17:07.285
Awesome!

17:21.587 --> 17:23.260
Mo.

17:49.615 --> 17:51.617
Stop it.

17:51.784 --> 17:53.127
Mo!

17:55.162 --> 17:56.880
- Rudy?

18:03.212 --> 18:04.714
What's going on out here?

18:04.880 --> 18:06.427
Mo made me push
one of the buttons.

18:06.591 --> 18:08.889
All right, well,
you can play with that later.

18:09.051 --> 18:10.519
- Your snack's ready.
- But I'm...

18:10.678 --> 18:13.306
Come on.
Soup's getting cold. Let's go.

18:16.225 --> 18:17.977
Come on.

18:40.958 --> 18:43.006
I don't think there's anything
Santa can bring you

18:43.169 --> 18:44.466
that will top that.

18:44.629 --> 18:46.176
This is the best Christmas ever.

18:50.009 --> 18:52.353
<i>- </i> What was that?
- Just a little wind.

18:52.511 --> 18:54.513
We're okay.

19:01.395 --> 19:03.489
Okay, that is
a hell of a storm front.

19:03.648 --> 19:05.195
We will turn right around.

19:12.031 --> 19:13.203
Mom!

19:13.366 --> 19:15.334
What the hell?

19:19.288 --> 19:21.882
J' Joy to the world J'

19:22.041 --> 19:24.669
J' The Lord is come... J'

19:24.835 --> 19:26.712
Come on, Larry.

19:26.879 --> 19:28.222
Is that really necessary?

19:28.381 --> 19:29.928
Hey, it's Christmas Eve, John.

19:30.091 --> 19:32.014
We've always had carols.
It's tradition.

19:32.176 --> 19:33.644
Now's not the time.

19:33.803 --> 19:36.397
Hey, I feel terrible about
what happened to Jacob,

19:36.555 --> 19:39.058
but you know how much
he loved this time of year.

19:40.059 --> 19:42.528
I wouldn't get between this man
and his decorations

19:42.687 --> 19:44.485
if I were you, John.

19:45.481 --> 19:46.733
I think this town
should just carry on

19:46.899 --> 19:48.071
in the Christmas spirit.

19:54.573 --> 19:55.745
Hey, Fred.

19:55.908 --> 19:59.037
- You fixed it!
- Fixed what?

20:00.413 --> 20:01.630
The clock.

20:01.789 --> 20:03.291
You got it going.

20:06.085 --> 20:07.962
Impossible.
I haven't touched it.

20:08.129 --> 20:10.257
Well, it's working now.

20:10.423 --> 20:12.721
No, you don't understand.

20:14.093 --> 20:15.561
I took the guts out years ago.

20:15.720 --> 20:17.848
They're in my shop.
It can't work.

20:22.143 --> 20:24.316
Whoa.

20:24.478 --> 20:26.526
What the hell is that?

20:29.024 --> 20:31.026
Mayday, Mayday, Mayday.
This is Alaska Charter

20:31.193 --> 20:32.993
November-101. We are
in a serious storm system

20:33.028 --> 20:34.780
at the bottom of Mount Thalberg.

20:44.874 --> 20:46.251
Jenn, I need your help.

20:46.417 --> 20:47.634
<i>- </i> What?
- I need you...

20:47.793 --> 20:49.136
I need you to find me
a frequency.

20:49.295 --> 20:51.047
You need to get a message out.

20:55.384 --> 20:58.263
Honey, go through
each frequency.

20:59.847 --> 21:01.207
Mayday, Mayday.
Can anyone hear us?

21:01.348 --> 21:03.897
<i>- </i> This is Jennifer Miller.

21:04.059 --> 21:05.777
Mom!

21:05.936 --> 21:07.938
You ever seen
anything like that before?

21:08.105 --> 21:10.483
No.

21:10.649 --> 21:12.947
Mayday, this is Jennifer Miller.

21:13.986 --> 21:15.988
- Mayday, Mayday!
- Jennifer, come in!

21:16.155 --> 21:18.374
Jenny, can you hear me?

