and look for him.

45:31.817 --> 45:33.535
Rudy?

45:36.614 --> 45:38.662
Rudy?

45:42.453 --> 45:43.796
Rudy!

45:50.962 --> 45:54.136
Rudy!

46:06.727 --> 46:08.229
You've got to be kidding me.

46:09.230 --> 46:10.652
That was no normal storm.

46:10.815 --> 46:12.658
I was thinking the same thing.

46:12.817 --> 46:15.070
Dad?

46:17.363 --> 46:19.115
These windows aren't gonna hold.

46:19.282 --> 46:21.410
- Hello?
- Did you hear that?

46:22.702 --> 46:23.828
- Anyone?
- It sounds like Derrick.

46:23.995 --> 46:25.588
Jenn!

46:25.746 --> 46:27.498
I need to get you out.
Hold on, guys.

46:27.665 --> 46:30.293
- Derrick!
- Derrick!

46:30.459 --> 46:32.837
I'm gonna get you out! Hold on!

46:33.004 --> 46:34.506
Derrick!

46:35.506 --> 46:36.883
Rudy!

46:38.884 --> 46:40.101
Rudy!

46:43.222 --> 46:44.974
Rudy!

46:57.486 --> 46:58.863
Come on.
It's not much further.

47:01.907 --> 47:03.409
Keep g0il19-

47:08.122 --> 47:10.341
This is Tully in the Town Hall
of Normal, Alaska.

47:10.499 --> 47:11.876
- Here.
- If you're receiving this,

47:12.043 --> 47:13.716
- Thanks.
- Please acknowledge. Over.

47:18.090 --> 47:19.592
You reach him?

47:19.759 --> 47:22.057
Nobody.
Not John, not anybody.

47:22.219 --> 47:24.221
The radio's working fine.
It's like...

47:24.388 --> 47:25.890
nobody can even hear us.

47:26.057 --> 47:27.684
How is that possible?

47:27.850 --> 47:29.147
I have no idea.

47:29.310 --> 47:30.653
Emergency teams
should have been here hours ago.

47:30.811 --> 47:33.530
It's like... it's like the whole town
just dropped off the map.

47:33.689 --> 47:35.817
So what are you gonna do?

47:35.983 --> 47:37.405
I'm hoping I wake up

47:37.568 --> 47:39.991
I'll get more supplies.

47:42.239 --> 47:44.958
This is Tully in the Town Hall
of Normal, Alaska.

47:45.117 --> 47:47.165
If you're receiving this,
please acknowledge. Over.

48:03.511 --> 48:05.138
I'm worried about Rudy.

48:06.430 --> 48:08.558
Mary's a smart girl.

48:08.724 --> 48:10.647
I'm sure Rudy'll be fine.

48:12.311 --> 48:13.984
Come on.

48:14.146 --> 48:15.693
We're almost there.

48:22.488 --> 48:24.331
- You okay?
- Yeah.

48:34.834 --> 48:36.427
You okay?

48:37.920 --> 48:39.342
Yeah.

48:39.505 --> 48:40.802
I'll live.

48:40.965 --> 48:43.013
I'm sorry about your friend.

48:43.175 --> 48:44.677
Yeah, me, too.

48:45.678 --> 48:47.521
Okay, let's keep moving, guys.

48:47.680 --> 48:49.978
Come on.
Let's go.

48:56.147 --> 48:57.615
Mayday, Mayday.

48:57.773 --> 49:00.447
This is Tully in the town
of Normal, Alaska.

49:00.609 --> 49:03.453
Is there anybody out there?
Please respond.

49:03.612 --> 49:05.034
Mayday, mayday-

49:05.197 --> 49:07.495
If you're receiving this,
please acknowledge.

49:07.658 --> 49:10.958
If anyone is out there,
please acknowledge. Over.

49:19.837 --> 49:21.214
If you're receiving this,

49:21.380 --> 49:23.883
please acknowledge.

49:25.050 --> 49:27.519
- Tully.
- John.

49:27.678 --> 49:28.975
Oh, thank God.

49:29.138 --> 49:30.560
Jennifer and Beth okay?

49:31.891 --> 49:33.438
They're both a bit banged up.

49:33.601 --> 49:36.104
We've got a casualty
on the mountain.

49:36.270 --> 49:38.864
Look, we need you in town.

49:39.023 --> 49:41.025
How quickly can you get here?

49:41.192 --> 49:43.320
We gotta check on Rudy
and then I'll be there.

49:43.486 --> 49:44.829
Okay. Hurl'Y-

49:44.987 --> 49:46.739
Okay.
Just sit tight, okay?

49:46.906 --> 49:48.283
Okay.

49:49.575 --> 49:50.952
Sit tight.

49:52.828 --> 49:54.250
Sitting tight.

49:55.581 --> 49:56.958
Rudy!

50:00.085 --> 50:01.462
Rudy!

50:04.590 --> 50:05.887
Hey' hey!
Stop!

50:06.050 --> 50:07.927
Stop the... stop!

50:08.093 --> 50:09.390
Stop!

50:13.682 --> 50:15.059
Mary, what are you
doing out here?

50:15.226 --> 50:16.466
Oh, thank God.
I have been going

50:16.519 --> 50:17.611
<i>- </i> out of my mind.
- Where's Rudy?

50:17.770 --> 50:18.896
<i>- </i> Where's Rudy?
- He's gone.

50:19.063 --> 50:20.064
What do you mean "gone"?

50:20.231 --> 50:22.450
I've searched for him everywhere
I can possibly think,

50:22.608 --> 50:23.655
<i>- </i> but I can't find him.
- Okay, okay. Calm down.

50:23.817 --> 50:24.943
Just tell us what happened.

50:25.110 --> 50:27.738
Mo ran away and I went to look
for him for, like, two seconds.

50:27.905 --> 50:29.705
And then when I came back,
Rudy was just gone.

50:29.865 --> 50:32.288
And he left me this note.

50:33.327 --> 50:34.624
"It's all my fault."
What was?

50:34.787 --> 50:36.130
<i>- </i> What was all his fault?
- I don't know.

50:36.288 --> 50:38.211
He was talking about
his snow globe.

50:38.374 --> 50:39.967
I tried to tell him
it was all nonsense,

50:40.125 --> 50:41.468
but he wouldn't listen.

50:41.627 --> 50:43.129
- He's alone out there.
- He can't have gone far. Come on.

50:43.295 --> 50:45.548
- We should split up.
- No way. We are sticking together.

50:45.714 --> 50:46.806
No, you guys
keep going that way.

50:46.966 --> 50:48.286
I'm gonna head over
to Maple Road.

50:48.300 --> 50:49.740
He's got a little hideout
over there.

50:52.638 --> 50:53.890
Makes sense.
You know it does.

50:54.056 --> 50:56.184
Yeah, I'll go with her.

50:56.350 --> 50:57.647
Okay, you're with me.
Whatever happens,

50:57.810 --> 50:59.530
- meet back at Town Hall.
- I'm coming, too.

50:59.562 --> 51:00.609
Mary, you should
go back to your family.

51:00.771 --> 51:02.114
No, I'm going.
This is my fault.

51:02.273 --> 51:03.820
I'm gonna help find him.

51:14.785 --> 51:15.911
Why is he blaming himself?

51:16.078 --> 51:17.876
What does any of this
have to do with him?

51:19.707 --> 51:21.880
He's got a very active imagination.

51:22.042 --> 51:24.636
What was Mary saying
about the snow globe?

51:24.795 --> 51:26.342
This morning, Rudy said
there was a crack in the globe.

51:26.505 --> 51:28.007
Just like there was in town.

51:31.302 --> 51:32.770
You think he imagined that?

51:32.928 --> 51:34.305
I don't know.
It sounds crazy.

51:34.471 --> 51:36.815
But he was right.
I mean, he had to know somehow.

51:38.434 --> 51:40.232
God, I hope he's okay.

51:40.394 --> 51:41.771
Rudy!

51:45.316 --> 51:46.863
Rudy!

51:49.194 --> 51:50.571
So this hideout that
your brother's got.

51:50.738 --> 51:51.910
What is it?

51:52.072 --> 51:54.825
It used to be
an old mine access.

51:54.992 --> 51:58.041
But if you ask Rudy,
it's his magic fortress.

51:59.455 --> 52:01.958
You know, from that silly
Dragon of the Crown.

52:02.124 --> 52:04.502
Oh, what are you talking about?
That game rocks.

52:05.794 --> 52:07.387
<i>- </i> Are you serious?
- Hell, yeah.

52:07.546 --> 52:10.265
Throw the crown in the volcano.
Kill the dragon.

52:11.634 --> 52:13.477
I grew up on that game.

52:15.012 --> 52:18.892
I guess my little bro isn't
as much of a dork after all.

52:20.601 --> 52:22.319
Rudy!

52:24.188 --> 52:25.781
Rudy!

52:31.320 --> 52:32.742
Derrick...

52:32.905 --> 52:34.407
are you okay?

52:35.574 --> 52:38.293
You know that Greg was
the closest thing I had to a brother?

52:41.830 --> 52:43.548
I mean, what's going on?

52:43.707 --> 52:46.301
How could any of this
be happening?

52:52.299 --> 52:55.223
You saved our entire
family today, Derrick.

52:56.720 --> 52:58.768
I wouldn't be alive
if it weren't for you.

52:58.931 --> 53:00.683
No one would have been
on that mountain if it weren't for me.

53:00.849 --> 53:02.522
No, if it hadn't been for you,

53:02.685 --> 53:04.938
we wouldn't have ever
gotten off that mountain.

53:07.606 --> 53:09.108
You saved us.

53:20.786 --> 53:22.788
Now help me find my brother.

53:27.793 --> 53:29.295
Okay.

53:43.976 --> 53:45.148
Rudy.

53:45.310 --> 53:47.312
Are you okay?

53:49.523 --> 53:52.493
<i>- </i> What are you doing here?
- I'm looking for you.

53:52.651 --> 53:55.746
Okay.
What can I do for you?

53:57.906 --> 53:59.908
Did... did you make this?

54:02.453 --> 54:03.670
No.

54:04.997 --> 54:08.547
<i>- </i> Jeez, where'd you get this?
- It came as a secret gift.

54:09.710 --> 54:11.007
My dad thought you made it.

54:11.170 --> 54:14.344
Me?
First I've seen it.

54:14.506 --> 54:16.679
It's exquisite.

54:16.842 --> 54:19.186
Everything that happens
inside here

54:19.344 --> 54:21.472
happens for real.

54:21.638 --> 54:24.016
- Is that right?
- You don't believe me?

54:24.183 --> 54:25.856
No, no.
It's just that...

54:30.856 --> 54:32.529
Well, that just...

54:48.707 --> 54:50.209
That just can't be.

54:53.003 --> 54:54.300
Rudy!

54:54.463 --> 54:56.682
- I know you're here!
- Rudy!

54:58.592 --> 54:59.844
Rudy!

55:01.720 --> 55:03.518
- Rudy?
- Rudy!

55:03.680 --> 55:05.557
Rudy!

55:07.392 --> 55:09.065
Let's get a closer look.

55:10.604 --> 55:12.356
Rudy!

55:17.069 --> 55:18.742
Rudy!

55:22.533 --> 55:23.785
Rudy!

55:27.579 --> 55:29.377
I don't think he's here, Jennifer.

55:32.292 --> 55:34.090
Tell you what,
we'll hang out for a bit.

55:34.253 --> 55:35.926
Maybe he'll show up.

55:38.757 --> 55:40.179
Okay.

55:48.225 --> 55:50.102
It's like
the Dragon of the Crown.

55:50.269 --> 55:52.943
The crown, it's cursed.

55:53.105 --> 55:56.575
So you think
this snow globe is cursed.

55:56.733 --> 55:59.202
Or maybe the globe
cursed the town.

55:59.361 --> 56:00.954
Yeah.

56:02.322 --> 56:06.077
And it's my fault
because I opened the present.

56:07.077 --> 56:08.954
Oh, Rudy.

56:09.121 --> 56:12.671
There are a lot of myths
about cursed objects.

56:12.833 --> 56:15.461
Sometimes the curse
is a punishment.

56:15.627 --> 56:17.675
Sometimes the curse is a test.

56:17.838 --> 56:19.306
But, I mean...

56:19.464 --> 56:22.183
even if this is a curse,

56:22.342 --> 56:24.595
it's not your fault.

56:26.638 --> 56:29.187
So you do believe me?

56:29.349 --> 56:31.443
Well, there's certainly
a lot of things here

56:31.602 --> 56:33.024
I can't explain.

56:33.186 --> 56:36.315
But the idea that this globe

56:36.481 --> 56:39.951
is somehow destroying
our town is just...

56:40.944 --> 56:43.538
I mean, there's no markings,

56:43.697 --> 56:45.950
there's no serial number.

56:46.116 --> 56:48.460
There's certainly no
"Made in China."

56:50.579 --> 56:51.751
I don't know about a curse,

56:51.914 --> 56:55.009
but this is certainly
the strangest thing

56:55.167 --> 56:56.840
that I have ever seen.

56:58.253 --> 57:00.472
Mayday, Mayday.
If anyone can hear this,

57:00.631 --> 57:02.474
please respond.

57:03.467 --> 57:05.970
If somebody heard you,
they'd be here by now.

57:07.930 --> 57:10.103
Larry, I'm...
I'm trying my best here.

57:10.265 --> 57:11.357
Look, Tully...

57:11.516 --> 57:13.314
whatever's going on
is gonna drag this town

57:13.477 --> 57:14.979
straight to hell
before it's done.

57:15.145 --> 57:16.665
Okay, Larry.
You're scaring the people.

57:16.730 --> 57:18.357
- Just...
- We gotta get outta here now.

57:18.523 --> 57:19.570
I understand that, Larry.

57:19.733 --> 57:21.093
But we can't really
leave right now

57:21.109 --> 57:22.269
until we get some assistance.

57:22.402 --> 57:24.370
Now everybody...
John.

57:24.529 --> 57:25.701
You've got a hell of a mess
on your hands here.

57:25.864 --> 57:28.367
- You can say that again.
- Rudy's gone. He ran away.

57:28.533 --> 57:30.035
- Has anyone seen him?
- Have you talked to Fred?

57:30.202 --> 57:31.749
Last time I saw him,
he said he was getting supplies

57:31.912 --> 57:33.539
- at his shop.
- You okay, Larry?

57:33.705 --> 57:35.582
I've had better days, John.

57:37.542 --> 57:38.982
Just calm down, everybody.
All right?

57:39.044 --> 57:41.718
We can't just sit around and wait.
No help is coming.

57:41.880 --> 57:43.882
<i>'</i> Rudy? Hey.
- Mom!

57:44.049 --> 57:46.268
We were worried about you, buddy.
You scared us.

57:47.552 --> 57:49.225
Oh, thank you, Fred.

57:50.681 --> 57:51.978
Yeah.

57:53.058 --> 57:56.403
Would you tell me
where you got this?

57:56.561 --> 57:58.359
I thought it was you.

57:58.522 --> 58:00.240
It was left at our door.
Why?

58:03.610 --> 58:05.658
Hell of a thing.

58:21.962 --> 58:23.214
Anybody answering?

58:23.380 --> 58:25.758
Phones are still dead.

58:28.927 --> 58:32.227
<i>- </i> What is that?
- Found it inside.

58:32.389 --> 58:35.233
Official Dragon
of the Crown issue.

58:35.392 --> 58:37.394
Face the dragon
without this bad boy,

58:37.561 --> 58:39.188
you can forget about it.

58:40.188 --> 58:41.906
Of course.

58:44.317 --> 58:45.534
<i>HEY</i>

58:45.694 --> 58:47.116
It's gonna be fine.

58:53.076 --> 58:54.453
Rudy?

58:57.831 --> 59:00.300
- Rudy!
- Rudy!

59:07.507 --> 59:09.430
It didn't look anything like that
the last time I saw it.

59:09.593 --> 59:10.810
Rudy's right.

59:10.969 --> 59:13.142
I can't quite believe
I'm saying this,

59:13.305 --> 59:15.023
but somehow,
what's happening in there

59:15.182 --> 59:16.684
is happening out here.

59:16.850 --> 59:18.193
It's not possible.

59:18.351 --> 59:20.319
Neither are about half the things
we've seen in town today.

59:20.479 --> 59:23.028
- You got that right.
- John.

59:23.190 --> 59:25.363
Townsfolk are getting antsy
and they're looking for answers.

59:25.525 --> 59:27.653
- Please tell me you got some.
- John...

59:27.819 --> 59:29.196
I think you should hear

59:29.362 --> 59:31.643
- what your son has to tell you.
- I'm worried about Jenn.

59:31.782 --> 59:33.329
Yeah, she should've
been here by now.

59:33.492 --> 59:35.292
You stay here with Rudy,
I'll go look for her.

59:35.327 --> 59:37.045
It'll be a nice change
from Town Hall.

59:41.333 --> 59:43.461
Tell us, Rudy.
What happened?

59:53.512 --> 59:54.809
A toy?

59:54.971 --> 59:56.723
A kid's toy
is what we're talking about?

59:56.890 --> 59:58.517
This is no ordinary toy.

59:58.683 --> 59:59.980
Just listen to what
we have to say, Larry.

01:00:00.143 --> 01:00:01.565
No, you listen up, John.

01:00:01.728 --> 01:00:04.197
We got a lot of dead
friends and family.

01:00:04.356 --> 01:00:05.636
Town's coming apart
at the seams.

01:00:05.690 --> 01:00:07.770
What does a damn snow globe
have to do with anything?

01:00:07.776 --> 01:00:09.198
Everything.

01:00:09.361 --> 01:00:11.489
Look, we've all known
each other for a long time.

01:00:11.655 --> 01:00:13.657
You just have to trust me
when I tell you.

01:00:13.824 --> 01:00:14.825
Everything that's happened
in this town

01:00:14.991 --> 01:00:16.709
- can be traced back to this.
- It's true.

01:00:16.868 --> 01:00:19.041
- Ridiculous.
- It's true.

01:00:19.204 --> 01:00:20.797
Now, ever since this thing
was placed at our doorstep,

01:00:20.956 --> 01:00:23.300
we've had one disaster
after another.

01:00:26.336 --> 01:00:27.804
Every time one
of these buttons is pressed,

01:00:27.963 --> 01:00:29.636
another disaster hits.

01:00:30.674 --> 01:00:32.017
And who told you that?

01:00:37.889 --> 01:00:39.391
My son.

01:00:42.227 --> 01:00:44.901
Look, if pressing buttons
causes disasters,

01:00:45.063 --> 01:00:46.861
then don't push
any damn buttons.

01:00:47.023 --> 01:00:48.866
It's not that simple.

01:00:49.025 --> 01:00:51.369
Have you looked
at the town clock today?

01:00:51.528 --> 01:00:52.905
It's ticking.

01:00:53.905 --> 01:00:55.407
Yeah, well, clocks
will do that, John.

01:00:55.574 --> 01:00:56.917
Not this one.

01:00:57.075 --> 01:00:59.123
You all know.

01:00:59.286 --> 01:01:01.084
I took that thing apart
years ago.

01:01:01.246 --> 01:01:03.715
There are no gears
inside that clock.

01:01:04.833 --> 01:01:06.551
And yet there it is,
ticking away.

01:01:06.710 --> 01:01:08.190
And it's got
the exact same time on it

01:01:08.253 --> 01:01:09.926
as the clock inside this globe.

01:01:10.922 --> 01:01:12.424
That's got to mean something.

01:01:15.051 --> 01:01:16.428
I think it's a countdown.

01:01:16.595 --> 01:01:18.768
Countdown?
A countdown to what?

01:01:18.930 --> 01:01:21.103
I'm guessing
at the top of the hour,

01:01:21.266 --> 01:01:24.270
another disaster's gonna strike
whether we push a button or not.

01:01:24.436 --> 01:01:27.485
Yeah, and maybe Santa
and his reindeers

01:01:27.647 --> 01:01:30.275
will come down from the sky.
It's all hogwash.

01:01:32.319 --> 01:01:33.445
Look out. I got it.
Go on.

01:01:33.612 --> 01:01:35.285
No, Larry...

01:01:48.335 --> 01:01:50.087
Didn't even leave a mark.

01:01:50.253 --> 01:01:51.800
- Here.
- Larry, Larry! No, Larry!

01:01:51.963 --> 01:01:53.886
Come here.
I need to talk to you.

01:01:58.762 --> 01:02:00.810
Mom, you believe me, don't you?

01:02:03.642 --> 01:02:05.440
Put down that sandwich
for a second.

01:02:09.481 --> 01:02:11.154
I believe that that snow globe

01:02:11.316 --> 01:02:14.365
somehow has something to do
with everything that's happening.

01:02:17.030 --> 01:02:18.873
And I believe that your dad

01:02:19.032 --> 01:02:21.911
will do anything to keep us safe.

01:02:25.956 --> 01:02:27.833
But I don't believe for a second

01:02:27.999 --> 01:02:30.001
that any of this is your fault.

01:02:32.003 --> 01:02:34.284
Getting everyone all excited
doesn't help anything, Larry.

01:02:34.422 --> 01:02:36.925
You said that thing just showed up
on your doorstep, right?

01:02:37.092 --> 01:02:39.052
Yeah, that's right.
Just showed up on my doorstep.

01:02:39.177 --> 01:02:40.724
No address, no shipping info.

01:02:40.887 --> 01:02:42.327
Yeah, then it's your responsibility.

01:02:42.347 --> 01:02:44.566
- You're doing this to us.
- Come on, Larry.

01:02:44.724 --> 01:02:46.522
You see what's happening
in our town.

01:02:46.685 --> 01:02:47.982
It's our problem.

01:02:48.144 --> 01:02:50.021
We're all in this together.

01:02:50.188 --> 01:02:52.862
- No, he's right.
- What?

01:02:54.109 --> 01:02:55.702
Okay, hang on here.

01:02:55.860 --> 01:02:57.533
Let's just say that I'm wrong.

01:02:57.696 --> 01:02:59.073
What are we gonna do?

01:02:59.239 --> 01:03:01.708
'Cause if you're right,
any minute now,

01:03:01.866 --> 01:03:03.834
another disaster's gonna hit us.

01:03:04.995 --> 01:03:07.669
Well, let's just hope I'm wrong.

01:03:16.881 --> 01:03:18.224
Rudy!

01:03:22.345 --> 01:03:23.813
Rudy!

